{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tipping-content-js","path":"/philippines","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Tipping is not required in the Philippines, except when the customer wants to show appreciation for services rendered. However, tipping is becoming more common especially in service-oriented places (spa, salon). In some restaurants and hotels, \"Service Charge\" (8%-12%) is included in the bill when issued; thus, a customer has the option to give an additional tip or not. In taxis, it is common to add 20-50 PHP on top of the fare.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/philippines","title":"Philippines","author":"Joni","date":"2019-11-22","image":"philippines.jpg"}},"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3333333333333333,"src":"/static/33318c7f71e54de67127d3568b0c9768/90537/philippines.jpg","srcSet":"/static/33318c7f71e54de67127d3568b0c9768/b3ebb/philippines.jpg 270w,\n/static/33318c7f71e54de67127d3568b0c9768/95b54/philippines.jpg 540w,\n/static/33318c7f71e54de67127d3568b0c9768/90537/philippines.jpg 1080w,\n/static/33318c7f71e54de67127d3568b0c9768/3cda3/philippines.jpg 1620w,\n/static/33318c7f71e54de67127d3568b0c9768/1f682/philippines.jpg 2160w,\n/static/33318c7f71e54de67127d3568b0c9768/651fd/philippines.jpg 3968w","sizes":"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"image":"philippines.jpg"}}}